    <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">The gap comes down to three things. Bristol agencies carry higher rents and salaries. Cardiff has more competing agencies, which oddly pushes prices up as they spend more on their own marketing. Swansea offers lower overheads and a business community where relationships are built on results, not corporate gloss.</p>

    <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">The important bit: lower pricing doesn't mean lower quality. Google's algorithm works the same in SA1 as it does in CF10 or BS1. The technical work, content strategy, and link building methodology are identical. Swansea businesses simply pay less for the same standard of work because the team delivering it runs more efficiently.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-semibold text-text mt-12 mb-4">What Affects SEO Pricing</h2>

    <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">Not every business needs the same level of investment. These six factors determine where yours sits on the pricing scale.</p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-heading font-semibold text-brand-light mt-8 mb-3">Competition Level</h3>
    <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">A solicitor going after "personal injury claims Swansea" faces far stiffer SEO competition than a dog groomer targeting "dog grooming Mumbles." More competition means more content, more links, and more technical polish to rank, which pushes the monthly investment higher.</p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-heading font-semibold text-brand-light mt-8 mb-3">Number of Keywords</h3>
    <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">Each keyword target needs dedicated on-page work, content, and performance tracking. Five keywords on the Starter plan is plenty for a focused local business. A company serving multiple areas across South Wales or chasing national terms will need the Growth or Enterprise plan to cover 15 to 30 or more keywords properly.</p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-heading font-semibold text-brand-light mt-8 mb-3">Current Website Condition</h3>
    <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">A well-built site with clean code, quick load times, and solid structure needs less upfront <a href="/technical-seo-swansea/" class="text-accent hover:underline font-medium">technical SEO</a> work. A site built on an ageing platform with broken links, missing meta data, and no mobile optimisation may need an initial technical overhaul before monthly SEO work can gain traction. Our <a href="/seo-audit-swansea/" class="text-accent hover:underline font-medium">SEO audit</a> tells you exactly where your site stands.</p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-heading font-semibold text-brand-light mt-8 mb-3">Content Requirements</h3>
    <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">Some industries call for substantial content production to build topical authority. A B2B company near <strong>Swansea Enterprise Park</strong> might need detailed case studies, whitepapers, and industry guides. A local cafe just needs Google Business Profile posts and location-page tweaks. The content workload has a direct bearing on which pricing tier fits best.</p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-heading font-semibold text-brand-light mt-8 mb-3">Geographic Scope</h3>
    <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">Targeting "plumber Swansea" is a single-location campaign. Targeting plumbing services across Swansea, Neath Port Talbot, Carmarthenshire, and Pembrokeshire means location-specific pages, separate Google Business Profile management, and broader link building. Multi-location campaigns usually sit in the Growth or Enterprise tier.</p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-heading font-semibold text-brand-light mt-8 mb-3">AI Search Readiness</h3>
    <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">Google AI Overviews, ChatGPT search, and Perplexity are changing how customers find local businesses. Optimising for these platforms takes structured data, entity-focused content, and citation strategies that go beyond traditional SEO. Our <a href="/ai-search-optimisation-swansea/" class="text-accent hover:underline font-medium">AI search optimisation</a> service tackles this head-on, and it's baked into all monthly plans at the appropriate level.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-semibold text-text mt-12 mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

